  "accepted_findings": [
    "Open-grown adult, intermediate, and forest-grown adult are independently generated static-mesh families with different deterministic seeds and authored live-crown, width, uplift, asymmetry, trunk, branch-count, and interior-density parameters; none is a transformed copy.",
    "The three forms read as materially different silhouettes in both turntable azimuths and at the 60 m and 150 m proxies.",
    "Bounded BarkBaseColorScale, BarkAOInfluence, LeafBaseColorScale, LeafAOInfluence, and LeafTransmissionTint controls improve leaf and interior-crown readability under fixed exposure without emissive fill.",
    "All fifteen Metal captures completed after a zero-error, zero-warning map check and no material compile errors."
  ],
  "rejection_reasons": [
    "Three crown-form prototypes do not satisfy the authoring contract for at least five adult variants and three intermediate variants across three age classes.",
    "The crowns still expose repeated horizontal shelf spacing and a procedural radial cadence, especially in the open-grown form; damage history, competition response, and crown gaps need per-instance structural variation.",
    "The closeups remain too sparse and diagrammatic for a photoreal foreground asset: twig and leaf density is low, branch intersections remain visible, and bark response still collapses too dark on the unlit trunk side.",
    "Temporal wind coherence, measured performance, ecology-set composition, and a source-matched corridor comparison remain untested."
  ],
